body: If I select "AppBar" in the code and then click External Documentation from the View menu, the browser will open this URL: https://api.dartlang.org/stable/1.20.0/index.html#id_AppBar

comment_data.body:
Thanks!

It looks like the Dart plugin hardcodes the documentation root to point to  `"http://api.dartlang.org/docs/releases/latest/"` as it's base root (`com.jetbrains.lang.dart.ide.documentation.DartDocumentationProvider#constructDocUrl`).

cc @alexander-doroshko for thoughts on how we might make documentation resolution a bit more retargetable.
Perhaps the dart plugin should complain if the library is not a `dart:` one?
Should be fixed in dart plugin. related: https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WEB-18284. //cc @jwren
Cool!  To be clear though, these are flutter docs.  Is there logic to redirect to `docs.flutter.io`?

It is `DartDocumentationProvider` class. Either it can be updated or flutter-specific `DocumentationProvider` could be added right to the Flutter plugin. In the latter case need to make sure that they do not fight with each other for the same PsiElement.
